<!-- 
  PLACEHOLDER IMAGE REFERENCES
  ============================
  
  This file documents the placeholder images used throughout the site.
  Replace these with your own nature photography.
  
  Required Images:
  ================
  
  1. /images/hero-forest.jpg
     - Full-screen hero background
     - Recommended: 2560x1440px minimum
     - Content: Dense forest, misty morning light, or peaceful woodland scene
     - Mood: Calm, inviting, slightly ethereal
     
  2. /images/forest-path.jpg
     - Used in "How I Help" section
     - Recommended: 1200x1600px (portrait orientation)
     - Content: Forest path, dappled sunlight, walking trail
     - Mood: Journey, invitation, natural progression
     
  3. /images/og-image.jpg
     - Social media sharing preview
     - Recommended: 1200x630px
     - Content: Brand logo over nature background, or compelling nature shot
     - Include text overlay if desired
  
  Image Guidelines:
  =================
  
  Color Harmony:
  - Images should complement the forest green palette
  - Avoid harsh, saturated colors
  - Prefer soft, natural lighting
  - Morning or evening "golden hour" light works well
  
  Compression:
  - Use WebP format when possible (with JPG fallback)
  - Aim for 80-85% quality
  - Hero images: keep under 500KB
  - Section images: keep under 200KB
  
  Tools for optimization:
  - Squoosh (https://squoosh.app)
  - ImageOptim (macOS)
  - TinyPNG (https://tinypng.com)
  
  Adding New Images:
  ==================
  
  1. Place images in /public/images/
  2. Reference as /images/filename.jpg in components
  3. For parallax images, use ParallaxImage component
  4. For section backgrounds, use SectionWrapper with hasParallaxBg
  
  Example usage in components:
  
  <ParallaxImage
    src="/images/your-image.jpg"
    alt="Description of image"
    height="500px"
    speed={0.3}
    rounded={true}
  />
  
-->

